# Portuguese and Play — Story Generator

A CLI tool that generates bilingual (PT/EN) short stories for each chapter of your A1/A2 and B1 European Portuguese textbooks. Each story targets the chapter's grammar structures, is written in a specific literary genre, and outputs a formatted PDF plus structured markdown with a full Portuguese version, English version, line-by-line interleaved translation, grammar notes, and vocabulary and verb conjugation tables.

---

## Setup

**Requirements:** Python 3.8+

**Install dependencies:**

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**Set your API key** (only needed if you're generating stories via the API — not required for `--prompts-only`):

```bash
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="your-key-here"
```

Add that line to your `~/.zshrc` or `~/.bashrc` to avoid setting it every session.

---

## Quickstart

### Generate all stories (calls the API)

```bash
python3 generate_stories.py
```

This generates 27 stories — 14 for A1/A2, 13 for B1 — and saves them as markdown and PDF files in `./outputs/`.

### Just export the prompts (no API key needed)

```bash
python3 generate_stories.py --prompts-only
```

Saves each story prompt as a `.txt` file, plus a single `ALL_PROMPTS.md` with every prompt in sequence. Use this to paste prompts manually into Claude.ai, ChatGPT, or any other LLM.

---

## All Options

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--book a1a2` | Only generate A1/A2 chapters (book 1) |
| `--book b1` | Only generate B1 chapters (book 2) |
| `--book both` | Both books — this is the default |
| `--chapter ID` | Generate a single chapter, e.g. `--chapter A1-1` |
| `--prompts-only` | Save prompts as `.txt` files, no API calls |
| `--dry-run` | Print prompts to the terminal, no files saved, no API calls |
| `--pdf` | Generate a PDF alongside each markdown file |
| `--pdf-only` | Build PDFs from existing markdown files — no API calls |
| `--inspire "TEXT"` | Provide a plot seed or inspiration for the story (see below) |
| `--inspire-file FILE` | Same as `--inspire` but reads from a text file |
| `--output DIR` | Output directory — defaults to `./outputs` |
| `--delay SECONDS` | Pause between API calls — defaults to `2.0` |

